Get rid of haemorrhoids and rectal discomfort in 5 days without pain or surgery

By Helen Parker, 14 November 2025

Haemorrhoids are among the most uncomfortable and commonly overlooked proctological issues. Sadly, many people are still unaware of how serious they can become. Most only seek help once the condition has already turned chronic or when painful inflammation develops in the surrounding tissue.

If treated early, more than 70% of complications such as infection, anaemia, and inflammation can be prevented. Theres no need to put your health at risk when you can relieve discomfort and restore normal function in as little as a week.

What is this actually about?

Haemorrhoids are small defects or swellings in the lining of the rectum. They often appear as tiny tears or inflamed blood vessels, causing pain, itching, and bleeding.

This issue can affect up to one in four adults in the US particularly pregnant women, office workers, smokers, those who are overweight, or anyone dealing with chronic constipation.

1. Mistake: Underestimating the seriousness of the problem

In the early stages, many people do not take anal fissures seriously and choose to ignore them, assuming they will heal by themselves.

This is one of the biggest mistakes you can make.

Untreated fissures can lead to abscesses, infection, or even anaemia. When the tear doesnt heal properly, bacteria can enter the wound and trigger inflammation and abscess formation.

If this isnt treated in time, surgery may be the only option.

2. Mistake: Relying on ineffective treatments

Many doctors in the US still prescribe the classic list of creams and suppositories for anal fissures.

But around 90% of these products only relieve the first symptoms itching, pain, or burning without removing the underlying cause.

The truth is that truly effective formulas are rarely found in ordinary pharmacies.

If everyone genuinely recovered fully, the pharmaceutical industry would not earn much from repeated prescriptions.

If you notice blood in your stool, pain or itching in the rectum, or a burning sensation during bowel movements, this is a clear warning sign.

You may only have a few months before inflammation develops into a more severe condition and at that point, ordinary creams or suppositories will no longer be enough.

Is there a solution?

One of the most effective products available is known as HemGuard Herbal Haemorrhoid Cream.

It is a deeply acting cream that helps heal anal fissures in just 5 days.

It can be used at all stages both for prevention and for severe symptoms such as itching, burning, bleeding, or rectal pain during bowel movements.

How can haemorrhoids be treated?

Treatment usually follows a clear and structured process.

First, inflammation and itching are reduced. Then, blood circulation in the affected area improves, allowing anal tears to heal naturally.

Over time, the damaged tissue begins to regenerate and regain its normal function.

It is important to highlight that this product offers an unusually long period without recurrence.

Although it is not possible to guarantee that fissures disappear permanently, most people experience up to 5 years without returning symptoms after completing the treatment.

This effect is linked to the body's own regenerative mechanisms.

The product helps the body restore a balanced, healthy state first by preventing recurrence, then by supporting the tissue in remembering the healed condition.

As long as heavy strain is avoided, such as chronic constipation or pregnancy, the problem typically does not return.

My recommendation

I strongly recommend that anyone suffering from haemorrhoids or anal fissures begins treatment as soon as possible.

The sooner you start, the lower the risk of complications such as inflammation, infection, or bleeding.

You can read more about the main properties of the cream, along with user experiences and expert opinions, on the official US website.
